tricks.description: By locking onto an enemy or scan point and strafing left or right, Samus' momentum can be maintainted. This is useful in crossing gaps.

By chaining multiple bombs, you can reach heights you wouldn't otherwise. Higher difficulties of this trick can involve horizontal movement, unmorphing in air, extremely precise bomb placements and timing.
Check the wiki for more details.

Jumping against a slope grants extra height when jumping, allowing access to ledges that are out of reach.
Check the wiki for more details.
This trick covers knowing the vulnerabilities of objects beyond their intended uses. Some examples include using Charged Hypermode to open the Seeker Missile locks in Command Vault.
A broad category for non-obvious movement which can't easily be classified using other tricks.

Bomb Jumping and unmorphing backwards to a wall or forwards from an overhang to get an instant unmorph, then jumping within 2/5 of a second after leaving the ground gives a height boost to reach higher ledges. Also works with Spring Ball.
Check the wiki for more details.

Rolling off a ledge, getting an instant unmorph, and jumping within 2/5 of a second after unmorphing grants speed and horizontal distance.
Check the wiki for more details.

Similar to a Roll Jump, except it does not require a ledge, and it requires Boost Ball. By morphing and barely tapping left or right on the stick, the camera desyncs from Samus. By boosting and jumping within the 2/5 of a second window, great distances can be covered.
Check the wiki for more details.

Morphing near a wall or a ceiling can cause Samus to be morphed without the animation, allowing access to Morph Ball tunnels from the back, or entering a tunnel unintended.
Check the wiki for more details.
Objects that normally can't be seen or accessed without X-Ray Visor, such as Phazite Barriers, can be possible in logic depending on the difficulty.
Some parts of the terrain can be abused and stood on, allowing access to certain areas otherwise unreachable.
Some terminal fall triggers can be used to warp to certain sections of a room, such as Crash Site.

Traveling outside the room boundaries to gain access to areas/rooms otherwise unreachable given the circumstances. Currently only used for single-room traversal.
Check the wiki for more details.
Some gates or barriers can be opened from reverse with certain techniques or items.

Using Screw Attack without Space Jump does not work as intended unless the Screw Attack is intiated specific rooms where Samus's position in the Z-Axis is 0.
Check the wiki for more details.

By performing a Boost Spring Space Jump through a door frame on some rooms in Elysia, the terminal fall trigger can be skipped and place Samus Out of Bounds.
Check the wiki for more details.
This trick covers traversal through Acid Rain and Fuel Gel without having Hazard Shield. Energy Tanks are used as a replacement.
Mainly used for bosses, requiring either less items or less health to beat a boss.
